  = Dosage Form Analysis of Top 10 Best-Selling Biologics in 2025
])

= 1 Abstract

The global biologics market has reached unprecedented levels in 2025, with
*monoclonal antibodies* and related biologic therapies dominating pharmaceutical
sales. This report analyzes the dosage form strategies of the top 10 best-selling
biologics in 2025 to identify common patterns in biologic delivery system
development.

= 2 Methodology

Data sources:
- #link("https://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/")[FDA prescribing information
    (DailyMed, Drugs\@FDA)]
- #link("https://www.ema.europa.eu/en/homepage")[EMA product information]
- Company press releases and annual reports (2024-2025)
- Scientific literature on biologic delivery systems.

= 3 Results

1. *SC Administration is the Dominant Trend*.

  10 of 10 top biologics offer subcutaneous administration. SC injection has
  become the standard route for biologic delivery due to:
  - Patient convenience (self-administration potential)
  - Reduced healthcare resource utilization
  - Faster administration time (minutes vs. hours)

2. *Dual IV $arrow.r$ SC Progressive Launch Strategy*

  $70%$ of top biologics offer both IV and SC administration. This *progressive
  launch* strategy allow companies to:
  - Launch IV first (faster regularity pathway)
  - Introduce SC later for lifecycle extension
  - Maintain market share before patent expiration

